That Pirates of The Caribbean II scene where Jack Sparrow is chained to the mast with Kraken sinking the ship as he struggles to escape by lubricating his handcuffed wrists with an oil lamp's grease is sublime. Struggle to survive at any cost, the oldest most primordial morality.
